originalText.text: Dr. Ritke is a truly gifted healer. She has healed muscle and joint ailments and internalized stress I had carried for years. The first time I came home from seeing her my children told me it was amazing, I looked decades younger and lighter of spirit. Rae is kind, calming, committed to healing her patients, expert at what she does, and always listens patiently and explains what she is doing. I am so grateful I found her, she is truly wonderful.

originalText.text: Rae was the therapist I dreamt of. Considering, flexible, thorough, thoughtful and caring. Her bedside manner is superb. She made me feel safe and comfortable but more importantly she helped me during my IUI treatment that resulted in a healthy baby boy. She knows what she is doing but she involves you in the process and makes sure you understand what she is working on and how long it might take to get results.

originalText.text: Rae is wonderful. Her presence and office is so calming. I love and look forward to the naps I take during the acupuncture sessions. I came after I had my gallbladder removed because I was so tired during recovery and she definitely helped with my recovery and digestion, and has since helped with muscle and other issues.

originalText.text: Rae is so phenomenal at what she does.  I've been to other acupuncturists in the past and none have the skill and bedside manner that Rae does.  I always come away from my sessions feeling more relaxed, rested and recharged. It truly is an investment in my overall health but especially helpful when I'm experiencing neck pain or issues with my sleep.  Be sure to give Rae and Urban Wellness a try - you'll be glad you did.
